Photo: James Nielsen, Staff Image 71 of 71 Joe Ely, Grady Gaines lined up for Discovery Green series 1 / 71 Back to Gallery West Texas music great Joe Ely will kick off Discovery Green's annual concert series with a performance in the downtown park on May 11.
As has become tradition, the series offers a diverse series of free, family-friendly shows on Thursday evenings throughout the summer. Other highlights this summer will include an inspired pairing of saxophone legend Grady Gaines with his Texas Upsetters and the storied ThunderSOUL Orchestra.
CONCERT FAIL: Promoter sues rapper after he no shows
Expect some first class guitar playing throughout the summer, too, including Del Castillo, a Latin rock ensemble driven by two brothers playing blistering solos on Spanish guitars; Texas roots and rockabilly mainstays Rosie Flores and Jesse Dayton; and Ian Moore, who can do breakneck blues as well as brisk power pop.
The full lineup for the summer:
May 11: Joe Ely with Brant Croucher
May 18: Del Castillo
May 25: ThunderSOUL Orchestra and Grady Gaines & The Texas Upsetters
June 1: Luke Winslow King with Kris Lager Band
June 8: Leyla McCalla with Chubby Knuckle Choir
June 15: Jesse Dayton with the Octanes
June 22: Rosie Flores with Sparky Parker
June 29: Ian Moore with Tony Vega
More information here .
